cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with word embeddings and language tasks such as sentiment analysis and question answering. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it uses PCA for dimensionality reduction. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as word embeddings are widely used in natural language processing tasks. It could also be classified under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as word embeddings are used in information retrieval tasks such as document ranking. Finally, it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as word embeddings are often trained using neural networks.
